Washington - Former US president Barack Obama says he supports the protests against President Donald Trump's immigration order.Weighing in publicly for the first time since leaving office on January 20, Obama says he is &quot;heartened by the level of engagement,&quot; according to a statement quoting Obama's spokesman Kevin Lewis.Lewis said Obama &quot;fundamentally disagrees with the notion of discriminating against individuals because of their faith or religion.&quot; He also rejects Trump's claim that his policy is similar to what Obama did in 2011 when he banned visas for refugees from Iraq for six months. dpa